defs.docs: A library for acquiring a backtrace at runtime

defs.name: trace_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `trace`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: Frame
defs.docs:
A trait representing one frame of a backtrace, yielded to the `trace`
 function of this crate.

defs.name: ip
defs.docs: Returns the current instruction pointer of this frame.

defs.name: symbol_address
defs.docs: Returns the starting symbol address of the frame of this function.

attributes.value:
cfg(all(not(all(target_os = "android", target_arch = "arm")),
          not(all(target_os = "freebsd", target_arch = "arm")),
          not(all(target_os = "linux", target_arch = "arm"))))

defs.name: resolve_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `resolve`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: resolve_frame_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `resolve_frame`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: Symbol
defs.docs: A trait representing the resolution of a symbol in a file.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of this function.

defs.name: addr
defs.docs: Returns the starting address of this function.

defs.name: filename_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the raw filename as a slice. This is mainly useful for `no_std`
 environments.

defs.name: lineno
defs.docs: Returns the line number for where this symbol is currently executing.

defs.name: SymbolName
defs.docs:
A wrapper around a symbol name to provide ergonomic accessors to the
 demangled name, the raw bytes, the raw string, etc.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new symbol name from the raw underlying bytes.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Returns the raw (mangled) symbol name as a `str` if the symbol is valid utf-8.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns the raw symbol name as a list of bytes

defs.name: Pcinfo
defs.value: Symbol::Pcinfo { pc, filename, lineno, function, symname }

defs.name: Bytes
defs.docs: A slice, typically provided on Unix platforms.

defs.name: BytesOrWideString
defs.docs:
A platform independent representation of a string. When working with `std`
 enabled it is recommended to the convenience methods for providing
 conversions to `std` types.
